<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08007</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING EMERGENCY RICE RESERVES AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to provide a contingency program in order to maintain a functional reserve of rice in case shortage exists in times of national calamity or emergency.
Tasks the National Food Authority (NFA) to effectively:
a)	Maintain and manage a government rice reserve equivalent to fifteen (15) days of the national rice consumption for the current year and determine the location and distribution of such stocks into depots nationwide;
b)	Procure stock from small farmers and farmersâ€™ cooperatives and import only under abnormal conditions;
c)	Release to the market said rice reserve upon the declaration of a state of calamity by the President.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SY-ALVARADO, JOSE ANTONIO &quot;KUYA JONATHAN&quot; R.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-08-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT ENTERPRISES AND PRIVATIZATION ON 2018-10-10</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON AGRICULTURE AND FOOD, FOOD SECURITY</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PREVIOUS COMMITTEE REFERRALS :PRIMARILY REFERRED TO FOOD SECURITY on 2018-08-08;</td></tr></table>